Visibility logic summary:
- `showSuggestions` is `true` when `status === 'idle' && promptSuggestions.length > 0 && input.length === 0`
- This means chips disappear when the user starts typing (`input.length > 0`)
- Chips disappear when streaming starts (`status !== 'idle'`)
- Chips disappear when `promptSuggestions` is cleared (on `executeSubmission`)
- Chips reappear if the user clears their input back to empty

Click behavior:
- `handleSuggestionClick` calls `setInput(suggestion)` — populates the input with the suggestion text
- Then calls `chatInputRef.current?.focus()` — focuses the textarea so the user can review and press Enter
- Does NOT auto-send — the user must press Enter to submit

